      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIGHT FOR VICTORY (8) could only manage to finish fifth at his latest appearance over 1660m at this track, failing to live up to market expectations. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. His recent effort is not a true indication. Good enough to put himself right in the finish. RED BULL BERNIE (6) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 2138m at this track, finishing second and just 1.4 metres from the winner. Meets a similar line up and he can figure in the finish. OPALLANE (5) is the next elect off a last-start win by 1.5 metres at Redcliffe over 1780m. DEGARMEA TEALE (7) comes here following a fifth behind Arrhythmia at Group Two level six-and-a-half months ago over 2240m at Melton. Proven performer against better opposition. Must be respected.",
